docs.abstract: In withdrawing complaints with authorities worldwide, the companies said they would try to resolve future disputes before protesting to regulators.
docs.snippet: In withdrawing complaints with authorities worldwide, the companies said they would try to resolve future disputes before protesting to regulators.
docs.lead_paragraph: SEATTLE — Microsoft and Google agreed on Friday to withdraw complaints against each other with regulators around the world, as the two American tech giants continued recent efforts to settle the once-bitter conflicts between them.

headline.main: Microsoft and Google Agree to Drop Mutual Complaints
headline.print_headline: Microsoft and Google End Mutual Complaints

docs.abstract: This economics of tiny things demonstrates the global power of the few companies, including Amazon, Microsoft and Google, that can make fortunes from the small.
docs.snippet: This economics of tiny things demonstrates the global power of the few companies, including Amazon, Microsoft and Google, that can make fortunes from the small.
docs.lead_paragraph: SAN FRANCISCO — Imagine building an enormous beach resort, maybe the best in the world. Instead of renting the rooms, you charge guests based on the grains of sand they touch. You charge very little per grain, but if they lie on enough of them, it adds up.

headline.main: Billing by Millionths of Pennies, Cloud Computing’s Giants Take In Billions

docs.abstract: The software giant argues in a lawsuit that law enforcement is too aggressive in seeking gag orders on its information requests.
docs.snippet: The software giant argues in a lawsuit that law enforcement is too aggressive in seeking gag orders on its information requests.
docs.lead_paragraph: Sometimes, you have to go on the offensive. That appears to be the thinking behind a lawsuit filed by Microsoft on Thursday against the Justice Department, arguing that the government is wrongly preventing the software giant from letting customers know when investigators armed with a court order have obtained customer data.

headline.main: Microsoft Goes on Offensive Against Justice Department
